         <abstract>
            <label>Abstract:</label>
            <p>In this paper we explore the Army’s Active Component Brigade Combat Teams’ (AC BCTs) unit <italic>Boots on the Ground</italic> (BOG) to <italic>Dwell</italic> ratio. In particular, we derive a closed-form result which is effectively independent of the underlying deployment schedule and deployment management technique. Using this result we show that the planned growth from 43 to 45 BCTs is insufficient to reach the Army’s targeted 1:2 objective for AC BCTs.</p>
         </abstract>
